The games that are simplest in concept are nearly always the most fun to play, and Color (sic) Switch is no exception. When this game first came out, it had just(!) 600 levels and a few modes of play, but its developers have kept it constantly updated and there are now 1,360 levels and around 10 different modes of play. Just when I think the concept has been exhausted, the creators manage to put a new spin on the idea and create yet another new mode. Grasped in seconds, the game will take much longer to master, particularly the later Zig-zag and Break levels. A strong sense of rhythm, a steady hand and considerable patience are absolutely essential for this game. Prepare for clammy hands as you work to  clear 1,360 levels, unlock 138 balls and accomplish 20 different achievements. Over 5 months and some 20,000 games, I've done the lot, so that leaves just the multiple endless modes for me; until they add yet more levels, that is.

This game is amazing I absolutely love the game itself, the quality is great, there are many different levels to choose from. There are many different game modes that are very enjoyable and will keep you very busy and entertained. However my one complaint about this game it that there are far to many ads. This game would have got 5 stars, but due to the fact it has so many ads I just couldn't rate it that highly. The ads are very disruptive, sometimes appearing in the middle of levels, which causes me to lose. The new mini game which has started up is extremely annoying. I have no care for fighting games and I hate the mini game that comes after every couple of times I've lost the game. It insists you play it and doesn't give you an option not to. If you really don't want to play the mini game, the only way to not play it is to close the app and to refresh it. Overall the game it's self is great fun and a brilliant idea but the ads are just very distracting and it caused me to only give this app 4 starts rather than the 5 stars I think the apprentice itself deserved. Please keep in my mind if you're thinking about installing this game that the ads truly are horrendous. The game is great however and very enjoyable. Please take my review into consideration, thank you😊

Color Switch is an amazing game. It's fun, addictive and challenging. There's a vast variety of balls and I always buy 'em when I can the chance to , I can't count the times I've caught myself spending all of my star points trying to find the right ball for me. There are also many of them that you can unlock by playing in different game modes, some harder than the others and more entertaining if I may add. The only thing that bothers me are the ads. I hate them! They constantly interrupt me while I'm trying to beat a level and it's getting on my nerves lately. The only way to actually enjoy this game is by turning your Wifi off, which I always do. The only reason I'd keep it on would be for my daily spin. I wish that the creator/creators of this game did something about it, because it's making many users unhappy and angry. Can't you guys just reduce the number of ads shown in this game? I'd rate this 5 stars if it wasn't for those annoying, idiotic ads. Overall, this game is really fun and I recommend it to anyone,!

My top three favourite modes would have to be Jump, Control and Gravity. Those modes are easy and  fun! I also like how to can buy new balls to play with. The money that you buy the balls with are stars, which you earn from each level while you're playing it. If you need more stars, watch a short video that is about 30 seconds long and earn yourself 30 stars! I also like that you can get a free spin every 12 hours to get stars or a mystery prize with! Also, if you are stuck on a level, skip that level by watching a short 30 second video! Another part of this game that I love is that you can play this game for infinity time! No levels!  Also, play the daily level! Play this game for free today! (I LOVE THIS GAME!)
